%% OptiCart auth flow — login, rotation, grace, reuse detection
sequenceDiagram
  participant B as Browser (memory token)
  participant A as Express /api/auth
  participant DB as MongoDB users

  B->>A: POST /login (email, password)
  A->>DB: bcrypt compare · isActive · isEmailVerified
  A->>DB: store SHA-256(refreshToken)
  A-->>B: accessToken (JWT 15m) + Set-Cookie refreshToken (httpOnly, SameSite=Strict, 7d)

  Note over B: access token expires → any request 401s
  B->>A: POST /refresh (cookie) — single-flight on the client
  A->>DB: findOneAndUpdate({refreshTokenHash: old}, {new hash, prev=old, grace 30s})
  alt exactly one concurrent refresh wins
    A-->>B: new accessToken + rotated cookie
  else token matches prevRefreshTokenHash within 30s (other tab)
    A-->>B: new accessToken only (no re-rotation)
  else stale token outside grace (theft signal)
    A->>DB: null ALL refresh hashes
    A-->>B: 403 AUTH_SESSION_COMPROMISED → full re-login
  end
